{"article_id":"QwS4KyrLH0HFxBr3","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Governors Divide By Party On Trump Plan","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"To Reopen Businesses","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"Shut By Coronavirus","depth":3},{"id":3,"text":"As the death toll from COVID-19 continues to rise ,","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"governors around the U.S. are figuring out how to reopen their economies","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"while still ensuring the safety of their citizens .","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"The White House released a three-phase plan on Thursday","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"that would provide guidelines","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"for when states might reopen .","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"In a call with governors , Trump said","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"states should begin loosening restrictions","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"after new COVID-19 cases have declined for least 14 days .","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"Trump has repeatedly said","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"that testing for coronavirus is a state responsibility .","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"Enthusiasm for the plan varied by party .","depth":5},{"id":15,"text":"Democratic governors generally said","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"it was far too early","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"to provide a timeline","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"for reopening ,","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"and they said","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"they wished","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"they had more testing support from the federal government .","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"Republicans ,","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"while urging caution ,","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"were more bullish about the possibility for a swift return to normalcy .","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"`` We appreciate their suggestions ,","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"and we will evaluate them thoroughly ,","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"but the plain overriding fact is we can not put the cart before the horse , ''","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"said New Mexico Gov . Michelle Lujan Grisham , a Democrat .","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"`` As CDC , FEMA , and public health experts across the country have made clear ,","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"we are not at a point currently","depth":12},{"id":31,"text":"where it would be safe to reopen ,","depth":12},{"id":32,"text":"and doing so prematurely would undo the heroic work of our health workers and first responders ,","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"endanger many more people","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"and essentially guarantee enhanced transmission of the virus ,","depth":14},{"id":35,"text":"leading to more illness and death . '' `` We can not do it","depth":14},{"id":36,"text":"without federal help , ''","depth":13},{"id":37,"text":"said New York Gov . Andrew Cuomo ,","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"regarding fully reopening the state 's economy .","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"Widespread testing will require supplies and hospital capacity","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"that the state does n't have ,","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"he said ,","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"accusing Trump of `` passing the buck","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"without passing the bucks . ''","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"Trump responded on Twitter :","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"`` Governor Cuomo should spend more time 'doing '","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"and less time","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"'complaining . ' ``","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"Washington state recently extended its stay-at-home order to early May .","depth":3},{"id":49,"text":"Democratic Gov . Jay Inslee told NPR 's All Things Considered","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"that two conditions would have to exist","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"before the state could reopen its economy :","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"`` No . 1 , we have to drive down the number of infections","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"so they 're as close to zero","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"as possible","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"so that we 're very confident","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"that there will not be a resurgence","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"that could overwhelm our hospitals , ''","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"`` The second condition is we have to have a comprehensive and robust testing and contact-tracing system . ''","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"Inslee said","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"the state is far from being able to meet either of those conditions .","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"The contact tracing system is dependent on being able to massively test the population","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"to see","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"who has been infected .","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"`` That testing capability does not exist anywhere in the United States right now , ''","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"Inslee said .","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"Colorado Gov . Jared Polis told NPR 's Morning Edition","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"that the federal guidelines resemble the plan","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"the state adopted the day before .","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"But Polis said","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"he wishes","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"that , like other countries , the U.S. had a national testing strategy .","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"`` Most other countries are doing it nationally , ''","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"said Polis , a Democrat .","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"`` I wish","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"that we had more help from the federal government . ''","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"When each state is responsible for testing ,","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"he said ,","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"the states end up competing against other states for supplies","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"- which drives prices up .","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"`` Of course it would be better to have a national testing strategy .","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"There 's no question about that .","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"But we 're not going to let the lack of one stand in the way of Colorado","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"doing what 's right , ''","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"Polis said .","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"In North Carolina , Democratic Gov . Roy Cooper said","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"he appreciated the White House 's guidance ,","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"`` but we still need the federal government to help with testing and personal protective equipment . ''","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"Oregon Gov . Kate Brown echoed other Democratic governors ' call for more federal assistance .","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"`` We are still in dire need of critical resources from the federal government ,","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"including sufficient personal protective equipment","depth":14},{"id":92,"text":"( PPE )","depth":14},{"id":93,"text":"and increased testing capacity , ''","depth":13},{"id":94,"text":"she said .","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"`` We have current , large unfulfilled order requests with the federal government for both PPE and testing materials ;","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"these are vital components","depth":13},{"id":97,"text":"to reopening Oregon","depth":13},{"id":98,"text":"and remain necessary","depth":13},{"id":99,"text":"to prevent a resurgence of the disease . ''","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"In contrast to Democrats , the response from Republican governors was more enthusiastic .","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"`` I think","depth":13},{"id":102,"text":"the president and his team are headed in a very good direction , ''","depth":13},{"id":103,"text":"said Tennessee Gov . Bill Lee .","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"Lee said","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"his state would use the same sort of gradual reopening strategy .","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"Iowa Gov . Kim Reynolds said","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"her takeaway from Thursday 's two-hour call between Trump and governors was that the federal government is a partner .","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"`` They are standing alongside us , ''","depth":14},{"id":109,"text":"Reynolds said .","depth":14},{"id":110,"text":"`` If there 's anything","depth":15},{"id":111,"text":"that we need to ramp it up","depth":16},{"id":112,"text":"and get our state 's economy moving again ,","depth":16},{"id":113,"text":"they stand ready and willing . ''","depth":14},{"id":114,"text":"Reynolds said","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"she was hoping to reopen the state 's economy sometime in May ,","depth":12},{"id":116,"text":"if possible .","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"`` I appreciate President Trump 's guidelines","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"for reopening pieces of the economy","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"that have been closed temporarily , ''","depth":13},{"id":120,"text":"said Nebraska Gov . Pete Ricketts .","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"`` It is critical that we get people back to work safely","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"and continue to slow the spread of the virus","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"as the country opens up . ''","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"Idaho Gov . Brad Little said","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"the president 's criteria for phased opening `` matches the criteria","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"we have been using in Idaho . ''","depth":12},{"id":127,"text":"The guidelines also confirm","depth":13},{"id":128,"text":"that Idaho is focused on the right areas for improvement ,","depth":14},{"id":129,"text":"Little said :","depth":15},{"id":130,"text":"expansion of testing access , contact tracing , and increased health care system capacity . `` Our collective efforts","depth":17},{"id":131,"text":"to slow the spread of coronavirus","depth":17},{"id":132,"text":"are working ,","depth":16},{"id":133,"text":"but we have not yet seen a prolonged downward trend ,","depth":14},{"id":134,"text":"as recommended by the president ,","depth":14},{"id":135,"text":"to justify opening up everything at once .","depth":13},{"id":136,"text":"Until we do ,","depth":12},{"id":137,"text":"we must continue to stay the course . ''","depth":12},{"id":138,"text":"Texas Gov . Greg Abbott announced on Friday a series of executive orders","depth":10},{"id":139,"text":"that would start to reopen shuttered businesses .","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"According to The Hill ,","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"that makes Texas `` the first state","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"to lay out a defined rollback of COVID-19 restrictions . ''","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"Retail outlets in the state will be able to open on Friday , April 24 ,","depth":9},{"id":144,"text":"as long as they can deliver items to customers ' cars or homes","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"in order to minimize contact .","depth":10},{"id":146,"text":"Texas will also loosen restrictions on surgeries ,","depth":8},{"id":147,"text":"permitting procedures","depth":9},{"id":148,"text":"that `` would not deplete the hospital capacity or the PPE","depth":10},{"id":149,"text":"needed to cope with COVID-19 . ''","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":299,"left":152,"right":298,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":152,"left":0,"right":151,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":151,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":298,"left":196,"right":297,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":196,"left":154,"right":195,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":154,"left":3,"right":153,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":153,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":195,"left":161,"right":194,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":161,"left":156,"right":160,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":156,"left":6,"right":155,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":155,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":160,"left":158,"right":159,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":158,"left":9,"right":157,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":157,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"context","nuclearit